    "recap_headline": "",
    "recap_text": "Baton Rouge, La. --\nAfter getting out to an early 4-1 lead, Creighton Baseball fell at #13 LSU in its first midweek game of the season on Tuesday, March 18.\nThe loss dropped Creighton to 5-8 on the season, while LSU climbed to 13-5.\nAfter LSU pushed across an unearned run in the bottom of the first, Creighton responded with two in the top of the second.\nBen North\ngot the Bluejays rolling with a single up the middle and moved to second on a failed pickoff.\nConnor Capece\nmade the error hurt with an RBI single up the middle, then immediately took second via a wild pitch. Capece scored later in the frame on a sac fly from\nLew Rice\n.\nCreighton extended its lead in the third as\nTeddy Deters\nand North drew walks, then Capece was hit by a pitch.\nIsaac Wachsmann\nfollowed with a two-run single to make it 4-1.\nLSU plated its second unearned run of the game in the fourth, but reliever\nShane Curtin\nclosed the door with another ground ball to move the contest to the fifth.\nThe Tigers took advantage of a little wildness from Curtin in the fifth as he loaded the bags on two hit batters and a single.\nJoe Hauser\ncame on from the bullpen, but was greeted by a grand slam from LSU's Omar Serna Jr. to give the Tigers a 6-4 edge.\nLSU tacked on two more in the eighth as Jake Brown launched his ninth home run of the season.\nCurtin took the loss, allowing three runs on one hit and two hit batters in one-third of an inning to fall to 0-2. LSU reliever Deven Sheerin earned the win (1-0) with 2.1 innings of scoreless relief, while Santiago Garcia picked up his first save with 2.2 innings of scoreless ball.\nThe Bluejays will remain in Louisiana to play a three-game series with Tulane beginning on Friday, March 13 at 6:30 pm."
  },
